### **Color Application Guidelines**

**Interactive Elements:**
- Primary buttons: Sage green background (#87A96B) with white text (#FFFFFF)
- Secondary buttons: Soft Clay background (#E8D5C4) with sage green text (#87A96B)
- Hover states: Darken sage green by 10%, Soft Clay becomes white
- Selected items: Soft Clay background (#E8D5C4) with 3px sage green left border
- Unselected items: White background (#FFFFFF)

**Text Hierarchy:**
- Main headings: Dark charcoal (#1C1C1C) in serif font
- Subheadings: Dark charcoal (#1C1C1C) in sans-serif
- Body text: Dark charcoal (#1C1C1C)
- Supporting text: Warm gray (#6B7280)
- Success text: Sage green (#87A96B)
- Error/warning text: Rust (#C65D00)

**Gamification Elements:**
- Progress bars: Soft Clay background (#E8D5C4) with sage green fill (#87A96B)
- Achievement badges: Sage green background with white icons
- Badge borders: 2px soft clay (#E8D5C4)
- Level indicators: Gradient from soft clay to sage green
- Points/scores: Sage green text (#87A96B)

**Cards and Containers:**
- Primary cards: Soft Clay background (#E8D5C4)
- Secondary cards: White background (#FFFFFF)
- Sidebar: Soft Clay background (#E8D5C4)
- Shadows: rgba(135, 169, 107, 0.1) - subtle green tint

**Data Visualization:**
- CO2 values: Large sage green numbers (#87A96B)
- Progress meters: Sage green fill on soft clay track
- Comparison bars: Sage green for user, gray for averages
- Icons: Sage green (#87A96B) or dark charcoal (#1C1C1C)

### **Figma AI Instructions for High-Fidelity Design**

**Setup Instructions:**
1. Create a new Figma file with 4 desktop frames (1440x900px)
2. Import color palette as design tokens
3. Set up typography styles with specified fonts
4. Create component library for reusable elements

**Component Creation:**
1. **Item Selection Cards**: 320px width, 80px height, 12px border radius
2. **Sidebar Widget**: 280px width, auto height, 16px padding
3. **Progress Bars**: 200px width, 8px height, 4px border radius
4. **Primary Button**: Auto width, 48px height, 8px border radius
5. **Secondary Button**: Auto width, 40px height, 6px border radius

**Design Specifications:**
- Use Auto Layout for all components with 16-24px spacing
- Apply subtle shadows: 0px 2px 8px rgba(135, 169, 107, 0.1)
- Background patterns: Import natural textures at 5-8% opacity
- Icons: Use Feather Icons or similar, 24px size, 2px stroke
- Ensure all text passes WCAG AA contrast requirements

**Animation Guidelines:**
- Hover transitions: 200ms ease
- Progress bar fills: 600ms ease-out
- Page transitions: 300ms ease-in-out
- Micro-interactions on buttons and cards

**Export Settings:**
- Components: Export as SVG
- Screens: Export as PNG @2x
- Create design system documentation
- Include spacing and sizing tokens

This prompt provides all specifications needed to create a warm, approachable fashion carbon calculator using sage green and soft clay colors, with clear instructions for both low-fidelity wireframing and high-fidelity Figma implementation.
